WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:08.000
♪ ♪

00:10.640 --> 00:12.520
[French hip-hop music playing]

00:31.960 --> 00:33.960
♪ ♪

00:45.360 --> 00:47.360
[indistinct chatter,
music continues inside vehicle]

01:03.920 --> 01:05.920
[music stops]

01:25.760 --> 01:28.280
MARTIN: ...admitting
that you killed Judith Gray.

01:28.320 --> 01:29.880
SIDNEY:
How did you find me?

01:29.920 --> 01:32.280
MARTIN: It doesn't matter.
The point is we did.

01:32.320 --> 01:34.040
SIDNEY:
It's my son's birthday.

01:34.080 --> 01:36.120
MARTIN: Does he know
that his father's a murder?

01:36.160 --> 01:37.560
SIDNEY:
Get out of my house.

01:37.600 --> 01:39.600
♪ ♪

01:56.840 --> 01:59.440
You're looking for Will?

01:59.480 --> 02:01.320
[laughs]

02:01.360 --> 02:02.800
What's so funny?

02:02.840 --> 02:05.120
SIDNEY: We could have saved
a great deal of time

02:05.160 --> 02:07.040
if you told me so before.

02:07.080 --> 02:10.200
Will is in Rwanda. Ruhengeri.

02:10.240 --> 02:11.720
GEORGIA:
Where?

02:11.760 --> 02:13.560
SIDNEY:
The red house

02:13.600 --> 02:16.480
with white pillars
just round the corner...

02:16.520 --> 02:18.320
[muffled grunt, dishes clatter]

02:19.680 --> 02:21.080
You okay?

02:21.120 --> 02:22.160
Sweetheart?

02:22.200 --> 02:24.120
[gasps]

02:27.200 --> 02:28.560
I'm fine.

02:31.000 --> 02:33.280
If you know what's good
for you...

02:33.320 --> 02:35.400
you will get far away
from this place.

02:36.560 --> 02:38.960
MARTIN: If you're lying,
we will go the general.

02:39.000 --> 02:41.240
We will tell him that
you killed Judith Gray

02:41.280 --> 02:43.840
and we will tell him
that you have been colluding

02:43.880 --> 02:47.480
with Pieter Bello against him.

02:47.520 --> 02:49.560
Then speak to him.

02:49.600 --> 02:51.840
I'll show you.

02:51.880 --> 02:53.880
[phone dialing]

02:56.760 --> 02:58.760
[Sidney speaking French]

03:02.360 --> 03:04.360
[whispers]:
What is this?

03:07.760 --> 03:09.640
WILL:
Hello?

03:12.440 --> 03:14.640
-Will?
-WILL: Georgie?

03:14.680 --> 03:18.400
Georgie, oh, my God,
is that you?

03:18.440 --> 03:20.000
Georgia.

03:20.040 --> 03:22.640
-I came here to bring
a present to your boy...
-WILL: Georgia!

03:22.680 --> 03:24.800
-Liars!
-WILL: Georgie? Georgia!

03:26.760 --> 03:28.640
I am surrounded by liars.

03:28.680 --> 03:32.520
Taking the mine from me,
working with Pieter Bello.

03:32.560 --> 03:34.560
How many others?!

03:34.600 --> 03:36.960
How many other lies
have you told, Sidney?!

03:37.000 --> 03:37.960
Wait.

03:38.000 --> 03:39.160
Let me explain.

03:39.200 --> 03:41.120
I took you from nothing.

03:41.160 --> 03:43.240
-MARTIN: Please, calm down.
-This is my reward?

03:43.280 --> 03:44.560
We have nothing to do
with Pieter Bello.

03:44.600 --> 03:46.760
We just want to know
about Will Mason.

03:46.800 --> 03:48.160
You attacked Judith Gray!

03:48.200 --> 03:49.600
Your mine was losing money.

03:49.640 --> 03:51.560
Everyone was taking.

03:51.600 --> 03:54.720
Now we start again and you keep
collecting your cut.

03:54.760 --> 03:55.800
More, you'll make more.

03:55.840 --> 03:58.000
I was going to tell you.

03:58.040 --> 03:59.960
MARTIN:
Jesus Christ! Go.

04:00.000 --> 04:01.000
Go. Go.

04:02.120 --> 04:04.040
Move.

04:04.080 --> 04:06.080
[Azikiwe shouting in French]

04:11.280 --> 04:12.640
[engine starts]

04:17.240 --> 04:19.560
[panting]

04:19.600 --> 04:21.120
[curses in French]

04:21.160 --> 04:24.080
♪ ♪

04:24.120 --> 04:26.120
[tires screeching]

04:29.080 --> 04:32.000
GEORGIA:
Jesus, it was Will, Martin.

04:32.040 --> 04:33.560
It was him. [panting]

04:35.360 --> 04:37.800
So, now what?

04:39.200 --> 04:41.160
GEORGIA:
I'm not drinking it.

04:41.200 --> 04:43.360
WILL:
Just sniffing it like a junkie.

04:43.400 --> 04:46.800
The Internet says, what, just
200 milligrams a day, right?

04:46.840 --> 04:48.080
Oh, that's very relaxing,

04:48.120 --> 04:49.760
measuring out your
morning coffee in milligrams.

04:49.800 --> 04:53.720
Aw, mummy's about to have
198 milligrams of coffee.

04:53.760 --> 04:55.360
[laughing]:
Just sh... Go away.

04:55.400 --> 04:59.840
I am an arse, but hopefully
I'm an arse with a job.

04:59.880 --> 05:01.800
You're gonna be great. Mwah.

05:01.840 --> 05:03.720
Hey, hands off my milligrams.
They're mine.

05:03.760 --> 05:05.800
No. It's for your own good.

05:05.840 --> 05:07.560
Good luck.

05:07.600 --> 05:09.560
[kisses]

05:09.600 --> 05:11.560
JUDITH:
So...

05:11.600 --> 05:15.720
Your last role was running
a consultancy business?

05:15.760 --> 05:18.800
-Yeah, in the travel space.
-Mm-hmm.

05:18.840 --> 05:24.200
And before that,
you were MD of another company.

05:24.240 --> 05:26.080
Yeah, I mean, well,
we had some bad luck,

05:26.120 --> 05:28.560
but, yes, before that,
I was a marketing director.

05:28.600 --> 05:31.360
Paderborn, Akrotiri...

05:31.400 --> 05:33.000
My wife was in the Army,

05:33.040 --> 05:37.600
so my career, well,
it just always followed hers.

05:39.640 --> 05:42.320
I-I love what you do here.

05:42.360 --> 05:46.560
And I know my CV's patchy.

05:46.600 --> 05:49.760
I mean, two failed businesses.

05:49.800 --> 05:53.360
I could roll out a long list
of excuses, but...

05:53.400 --> 05:55.160
you know, it is what it is.

05:55.200 --> 05:58.640
The truth is it's my turn now.

05:58.680 --> 06:01.640
You see, my wife has been
supporting us for a long time,

06:01.680 --> 06:04.960
and... well,

06:05.000 --> 06:06.960
um, we're about to have
a baby soon.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.560
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

06:09.600 --> 06:12.160
So I need this job.

06:12.200 --> 06:14.440
And, Judith, no one
is gonna work harder for you

06:14.480 --> 06:16.040
than what I will.

06:16.080 --> 06:18.680
Because if I, if I fail you,

06:18.720 --> 06:22.360
then I fail my wife
and I fail my unborn daughter.

06:22.400 --> 06:25.360
And what's a better
motivator than that?

06:27.400 --> 06:30.880
The job does require some
occasional travel to the DRC,

06:30.920 --> 06:33.200
just to keep in touch
with what we're doing out there.

06:33.240 --> 06:34.480
Would you be okay with that?

06:34.520 --> 06:38.840
I'll do whatever
you need me to do.

06:38.880 --> 06:40.880
♪ ♪

06:55.880 --> 06:57.680
[tires screech]

07:02.680 --> 07:03.920
Mr. Benson.

07:03.960 --> 07:05.720
-What's the matter?
-The girl who was here.

07:05.760 --> 07:07.920
-Adidja?
-She left. I saw her running.

07:07.960 --> 07:10.600
-She carried a big bag with her.
-Well, why didn't you stop her?

07:10.640 --> 07:12.640
I followed her,
but she was too far ahead.

07:12.680 --> 07:14.800
-I lost her in the market.
-[sighs]: Oh, fuck.

07:14.840 --> 07:17.120
-I'm sorry.
-That's all right, Jean-Pierre.

07:17.160 --> 07:18.520
You can go. We--

07:18.560 --> 07:19.920
-Georgia!
-Well, she must've overheard us

07:19.960 --> 07:21.640
talking about finding her
somewhere else to stay.

07:21.680 --> 07:23.000
No, she's tough.

07:23.040 --> 07:25.240
She's a survivor.
She will be okay.

07:25.280 --> 07:27.520
She's a little girl.
She's on her own in a city.

07:27.560 --> 07:28.880
Yes, I know, and she's not

07:28.920 --> 07:31.040
your responsibility, Georgia.

07:31.080 --> 07:33.840
I'll stay here
and look for Adidja.

07:33.880 --> 07:35.920
You go find Will.
You heard the man--

07:35.960 --> 07:38.640
red house, white pillars,

07:38.680 --> 07:42.360
round the corner from the
New Market in Ruhengeri, Rwanda.

08:07.760 --> 08:10.000
-Georgia Wells?
-Yeah.

08:10.040 --> 08:11.960
Emery Security.

08:12.000 --> 08:13.520
Thanks for meeting me.

08:13.560 --> 08:15.080
Ruhengeri is not far from here.

08:15.120 --> 08:17.160
Uh, please follow me.

08:21.800 --> 08:23.840
Thanks.

08:51.520 --> 08:53.520
♪ ♪

09:13.480 --> 09:15.480
♪ ♪

09:28.800 --> 09:31.280
We're in the correct place?

09:31.320 --> 09:33.320
Yeah. I think so.

09:45.920 --> 09:48.320
Madam.
Madam.

09:48.360 --> 09:50.560
Can I help you?

09:50.600 --> 09:53.040
Uh, sorry, I-I think

09:53.080 --> 09:55.440
I've got the wrong house.

09:55.480 --> 09:56.960
Sorry.

10:00.000 --> 10:01.160
THIERRY:
What now?

10:01.200 --> 10:03.200
We try again later.

10:08.640 --> 10:10.200
MARTIN:
Her name's Adidja.

10:10.240 --> 10:12.720
She's 11 years old.
She went missing this morning.

10:12.760 --> 10:14.480
But I have a description
and a photo.

10:14.520 --> 10:16.720
Ask your officers to look at it.

10:16.760 --> 10:19.200
She's probably
still in the area.

10:19.240 --> 10:22.040
I'm wasting my time, really.

10:24.000 --> 10:25.600
God.

10:32.800 --> 10:34.680
[phone rings]

10:34.720 --> 10:36.680
Hi. How's it going?

10:36.720 --> 10:38.160
MARTIN [laughs]:
You might well ask.

10:38.200 --> 10:39.640
I just made the mistake
of trying

10:39.680 --> 10:41.160
to get some sense
out of the police.

10:41.200 --> 10:42.800
-No progress?
-No.

10:42.840 --> 10:44.880
They're not interested
in anything I have to tell them.

10:44.920 --> 10:48.640
Feels like I'm hitting
a brick wall wherever I turn.

10:48.680 --> 10:50.200
GEORGIA:
Sorry.

10:50.240 --> 10:52.360
Yeah, well, there's a lot
of that going around.

10:52.400 --> 10:53.920
GEORGIA:
Any news on Ariel?

10:53.960 --> 10:55.320
No.
[clears throat]

10:55.360 --> 10:56.840
Sadly, no.

10:56.880 --> 10:58.200
[sniffs]

10:58.240 --> 10:59.480
What about you?

10:59.520 --> 11:01.240
How are things where you are?

11:01.280 --> 11:03.360
I haven't been able to get
into the house yet.

11:03.400 --> 11:06.520
It's being guarded,
but I'm going to.

11:06.560 --> 11:08.200
Don't do anything stupid.

11:08.240 --> 11:10.080
Bit late for that, isn't it?

11:10.120 --> 11:12.120
Now, I think,
would be a good time.

11:16.800 --> 11:20.160
Looks like he's run out
of cigarettes.

11:20.200 --> 11:21.360
Come on.

11:21.400 --> 11:22.880
I have to go, Martin.

11:22.920 --> 11:25.520
All right. Bye.

11:25.560 --> 11:27.560
B-Bye.

11:45.480 --> 11:47.520
[tires squeak]

11:50.080 --> 11:52.240
[Georgia breathing heavily]

11:52.280 --> 11:56.000
Go. I'll keep him busy
as long as I can.

12:08.040 --> 12:10.040
[metal squeaks]

12:23.000 --> 12:26.360
[electricity buzzing]

12:26.400 --> 12:28.360
[glass shatters]

12:28.400 --> 12:30.360
[scraping]

12:30.400 --> 12:32.400
[thudding]

12:41.200 --> 12:43.200
[panting]

13:08.120 --> 13:10.120
♪ ♪

13:21.040 --> 13:22.600
WILL:
I'm off.

13:22.640 --> 13:24.560
Again.

13:26.400 --> 13:29.200
It's work,
and we need the money.

13:29.240 --> 13:31.000
That's right.

13:31.040 --> 13:33.000
Remind me
how useless I am. Nice.

13:33.040 --> 13:35.400
I don't have a choice.

13:35.440 --> 13:37.400
It's just...

13:37.440 --> 13:39.640
That's what I'm saying.

13:45.840 --> 13:47.800
We need to take
this down, Georgie.

13:47.840 --> 13:49.600
-Uh-- no, no.
-It's been a year, okay?

13:49.640 --> 13:51.600
It's not good for either of us.

13:51.640 --> 13:53.800
So, what, we just take it down
and then we forget about her?

13:53.840 --> 13:57.840
It's just a mobile.

13:57.880 --> 14:00.480
No.

14:07.360 --> 14:09.760
I'll call you when I land.

14:11.320 --> 14:13.320
[door opens]

14:16.320 --> 14:18.720
[door closes]

14:21.280 --> 14:24.240
[door opens]

14:24.280 --> 14:25.960
[door closes]

14:26.000 --> 14:28.000
[breathing heavily]

14:30.000 --> 14:32.000
[keys clatter]

14:38.040 --> 14:40.360
Will?

14:43.760 --> 14:47.480
Georgie?

14:47.520 --> 14:50.400
I can't believe it's really you.

14:54.080 --> 14:56.080
[crying softly]

14:56.120 --> 14:58.560
I found you.

14:58.600 --> 15:02.480
You're alive.

15:02.520 --> 15:04.800
Georgia, w-wait.

15:04.840 --> 15:08.440
I wish you hadn't have come.

15:10.280 --> 15:12.560
I don't understand.

15:15.800 --> 15:17.760
What's going on here, Will?

15:17.800 --> 15:19.400
Why are you looking at me
like that?

15:19.440 --> 15:21.000
Georgia, you shouldn't be here.

15:21.040 --> 15:23.560
Come on.

15:23.600 --> 15:25.040
Three years.

15:25.080 --> 15:27.400
Three years
I thought you were dead.

15:27.440 --> 15:29.120
-I'm sorry.
-I know you're scared.

15:29.160 --> 15:30.680
It's okay. I'm here.

15:30.720 --> 15:33.080
I'm here and I'm gonna
take you home.

15:33.120 --> 15:36.560
Who are you afraid of?
Is it the man outside?

15:36.600 --> 15:38.960
The man with the gun?

15:42.000 --> 15:44.280
Georgie, he works for me.

15:45.720 --> 15:48.360
There's a lot you need to know.

15:48.400 --> 15:51.400
[turbine whirring]

15:56.000 --> 15:58.000
[TV playing indistinctly]

16:02.760 --> 16:04.760
[cheering]

16:07.920 --> 16:09.880
PIETER:
Again.

16:09.920 --> 16:14.720
Right away, Mr. Tequila.

16:20.120 --> 16:24.000
Not a Sharks fan, huh?

16:24.040 --> 16:26.000
I like them when they lose.

16:26.040 --> 16:30.120
My lot kicked their arses
last time we played. Brumbies.

16:30.160 --> 16:31.920
I'm a Lions man, myself.

16:31.960 --> 16:34.280
I think we play you guys
in a couple of weeks.

16:34.320 --> 16:37.640
Yeah. You mind?

16:45.320 --> 16:47.320
Cheers.

16:54.800 --> 16:57.200
You're Pieter Bello, right?

17:05.480 --> 17:07.440
Have we met?

17:07.480 --> 17:11.040
Will Mason.

17:11.080 --> 17:14.040
No, we haven't met.

17:14.080 --> 17:16.080
But we have a friend in common.

17:17.400 --> 17:19.280
Judith Gray.

17:19.320 --> 17:21.480
I don't know anybody
called Judith Gray.

17:21.520 --> 17:24.600
[laughs]

17:24.640 --> 17:27.160
Then why is she paying you?

17:28.160 --> 17:32.160
DRC Aid, her company,

17:32.200 --> 17:34.440
has a ton of other companies.

17:34.480 --> 17:39.240
But if you follow the money,

17:39.280 --> 17:43.960
it leads you
into Bulletscreen Security.

17:44.000 --> 17:46.480
Owned by you.

17:46.520 --> 17:49.240
I think you must leave.

17:49.280 --> 17:51.600
Judith's making
a lot of money...

17:51.640 --> 17:53.880
[exhales]

17:53.920 --> 17:56.240
...and it's not
from her charity. Look.

17:56.280 --> 17:58.040
See that right there? Look.

17:58.080 --> 18:00.120
That is just last month.

18:00.160 --> 18:03.040
And you can see
what she's given you.

18:03.080 --> 18:06.800
It's quite
a big difference, right?

18:10.320 --> 18:13.400
I just want to know where
she's getting her money from.

18:13.440 --> 18:16.360
Now, why would I tell you that?

18:16.400 --> 18:18.520
It's quite simple, really.

18:18.560 --> 18:21.120
You tell me what I need to know,
and that figure,

18:21.160 --> 18:24.720
that figure that you get paid,
it goes up.

18:24.760 --> 18:27.080
I can increase
your cut every month,

18:27.120 --> 18:30.720
and Judith will never know
you told me a thing.

18:30.760 --> 18:32.880
And I'm not threatening you,
Pieter.

18:32.920 --> 18:35.320
I'm making you an offer.

18:37.960 --> 18:39.960
[patrons cheering]

18:44.760 --> 18:46.720
JUDITH: How was the flight to Kinshasa?

18:46.760 --> 18:48.440
-WILL: Yeah, good.
-JUDITH: Good.

18:48.480 --> 18:49.880
-JUDITH: Here, you want water? -Ah, yeah, thanks.

18:53.000 --> 18:55.480
There you go.

18:55.520 --> 18:57.520
Cheers.

18:59.400 --> 19:02.200
So, Judith?

19:02.240 --> 19:04.000
Mm-hmm?

19:04.040 --> 19:08.200
Tell me...
when did you decide to start

19:08.240 --> 19:10.560
smuggling coltan
over the border?

19:12.880 --> 19:14.440
Excuse me?

19:14.480 --> 19:17.440
You smuggle coltan to Rwanda

19:17.480 --> 19:20.440
in whatever charity vehicle
you can find.

19:20.480 --> 19:22.240
Your own when you have to.

19:22.280 --> 19:25.400
And then you sell it on
without the Congolese tax.

19:25.440 --> 19:28.400
It's a mine near Goma
run by General Azikiwe.

19:28.440 --> 19:30.400
You're helping him
rip off the government

19:30.440 --> 19:32.800
to line both your pockets.

19:35.920 --> 19:37.840
-Is that right?
-Mm-hmm.

19:37.880 --> 19:39.880
And if you don't
let me help you,

19:39.920 --> 19:42.680
you're gonna get caught.

19:42.720 --> 19:44.680
You need to launder the money.

19:44.720 --> 19:46.680
And a few shell companies
aren't enough.

19:46.720 --> 19:49.440
You need to scale up
the U.K. side of your charity,

19:49.480 --> 19:52.280
run the money through that
till it comes out clean.

19:52.320 --> 19:56.040
Cut me in every month,
and I'll help wash the cash

19:56.080 --> 19:57.280
through the U.K. side
of the business.

19:57.320 --> 19:59.040
-We can...
-You can stop now.

19:59.080 --> 20:01.680
-Stop what?
-Pretending you're here
to help me.

20:01.720 --> 20:02.720
Listen.

20:02.760 --> 20:03.720
[sniffs]

20:03.760 --> 20:06.080
It's simple to do.

20:06.120 --> 20:08.480
I, I open up
another two branches...

20:08.520 --> 20:10.080
Yeah, just cut it out, will you?

20:10.120 --> 20:12.560
Tell me what you will do
if I don't want your help.

20:12.600 --> 20:16.080
-But you need it.
-But what if I don't?

20:16.120 --> 20:18.400
You're not helping me, Will.

20:18.440 --> 20:20.760
You're blackmailing me.

20:20.800 --> 20:23.160
I'm not...

20:23.200 --> 20:25.760
Okay, um...

20:25.800 --> 20:27.560
Judith.

20:27.600 --> 20:31.120
You know what I've been through
over the last year.

20:31.160 --> 20:33.720
I've been following Georgia
from army base to army base

20:33.760 --> 20:37.720
for as long as I can remember,
and now this is my chance.

20:37.760 --> 20:40.520
To start again and to help.

20:40.560 --> 20:43.560
Yeah, well, we all have
our reasons, don't we?

20:48.280 --> 20:52.000
So, go on, then.
Name your price.

20:52.040 --> 20:54.960
WILL: She started paying me
to keep quiet.

20:55.000 --> 20:56.840
I kept the money in Kinshasa,

20:56.880 --> 20:58.840
another name
so it couldn't be traced.

20:58.880 --> 21:02.800
A year later,
I went out to visit Goma.

21:02.840 --> 21:04.800
The flight back was Sankuru 19.

21:04.840 --> 21:06.600
GEORGIA [over phone]:
You at the airport?

21:06.640 --> 21:08.520
I've got a couple of hours
before my flight to Kinshasa.

21:08.560 --> 21:10.120
Oh, well, you can hit the shops.

21:10.160 --> 21:12.480
-"Shop," singular. Oh, shit.
-[pencil clatters]

21:14.600 --> 21:16.560
Thank you.

21:16.600 --> 21:18.360
How's that ring feeling?

21:18.400 --> 21:19.760
Did I get the right size?

21:19.800 --> 21:21.800
[laughs]

21:31.440 --> 21:32.800
[whispers]:
Hey.

21:35.400 --> 21:38.760
[excited chatter]

21:38.800 --> 21:41.120
[phone ringing and buzzing]

21:41.160 --> 21:42.560
[speaking foreign language]

21:45.080 --> 21:46.240
Hey, Pieter.

21:46.280 --> 21:48.440
Yeah, guess what.

21:48.480 --> 21:50.120
That guy, um, Dikembe
is on my flight.

21:50.160 --> 21:52.160
PIETER:
Have you boarded yet?

21:52.200 --> 21:54.640
-No, not yet.
-Don't.

21:54.680 --> 21:57.080
I'm telling you, do not get
on that plane. You understand?

21:57.120 --> 21:59.400
Yeah, well, this is the last
flight out today, so,

21:59.440 --> 22:01.080
if I miss it,
Georgia will kill me.

22:01.120 --> 22:03.280
Listen to me, bru,
you've been straight with me.

22:03.320 --> 22:05.640
When you went to Judith,
you kept me out of it.

22:05.680 --> 22:07.480
And my bank balance went up
thanks to you.

22:07.520 --> 22:11.200
So let me return the favor.
Do not get on that plane.

22:11.240 --> 22:12.640
[phone beeps]

22:18.960 --> 22:20.960
[woman speaking French
over P.A.]

22:26.280 --> 22:28.280
[crowd chattering lightly]

22:46.040 --> 22:48.040
[breathing heavily]

22:51.400 --> 22:53.400
♪ ♪

22:57.880 --> 23:01.800
-Taxi.
-Yes, boss.

23:01.840 --> 23:03.360
Drive.

23:03.400 --> 23:04.640
[engine starts]

23:14.000 --> 23:15.400
We need to leave.

23:15.440 --> 23:16.720
The port door is closed,

23:16.760 --> 23:18.760
but I just need to confirm
the passengers.

23:18.800 --> 23:22.480
If we don't leave now we won't
be able to take off for hours.

23:22.520 --> 23:25.080
There's a big storm over Kindu.

23:25.120 --> 23:26.280
We need to leave now!

23:30.400 --> 23:33.640
[line ringing]

23:33.680 --> 23:36.120
PIETER: It's Pieter Bello,
leave a message.

23:36.160 --> 23:39.120
It's me. I'm off.

23:39.160 --> 23:40.480
Hey, can you call me back

23:40.520 --> 23:41.960
and tell me what the hell
just happened?

23:45.760 --> 23:47.320
[all screaming]

24:13.280 --> 24:15.280
[rumbling]

24:19.680 --> 24:21.680
[shuddering sigh]

24:29.840 --> 24:32.560
Okay, but none of this
explains why you allowed

24:32.600 --> 24:34.160
your wife to think
that you were dead.

24:34.200 --> 24:38.520
Yeah, well, the plane, it-it
had, had nothing to do with me.

24:38.560 --> 24:40.400
There was a politician,
Dikembe Rahema,

24:40.440 --> 24:42.000
who was on a mission
to clean up the East,

24:42.040 --> 24:44.840
which threatened to put
Azikiwe's operation in trouble.

24:44.880 --> 24:47.920
Now he had security
with him 24/7, Georgia.

24:47.960 --> 24:49.440
So, Azikiwe just...

24:51.360 --> 24:53.520
well he brought down
that whole 737.

24:53.560 --> 24:54.760
For one person.

24:58.240 --> 24:59.880
And Judith bought me the ticket.

24:59.920 --> 25:02.040
She must have just been sick
of cutting me in on it

25:02.080 --> 25:04.840
and thought,
"Two birds with one stone."

25:04.880 --> 25:07.400
Georgia, she tried
to have me killed.

25:10.080 --> 25:13.320
What, then you just,
you just walked away?

25:13.360 --> 25:15.280
You didn't look back?
You didn't...

25:15.320 --> 25:16.600
stop to think what could happen?

25:16.640 --> 25:20.080
As it sank in, Georgie, I just--

25:20.120 --> 25:21.840
I totally lost my shit;
I was a mess.

25:21.880 --> 25:23.400
-Fuck's sake!
-What?

25:23.440 --> 25:25.440
Pieter, he checked
the manifest of the crash,

25:25.480 --> 25:29.240
and... they screwed up, Georgia,
they counted me on the plane.

25:29.280 --> 25:31.240
I don't know why-- maybe
because of the politician--

25:31.280 --> 25:32.880
but he told me
like it was good news.

25:32.920 --> 25:34.920
That Judith and Azikiwe
wouldn't look for me anymore.

25:34.960 --> 25:36.640
That I was safe.

25:36.680 --> 25:39.560
But I couldn't even think,
I couldn't hear it.

25:39.600 --> 25:40.880
I wasn't.

25:40.920 --> 25:42.920
So, why didn't you
call me, then?

25:42.960 --> 25:44.400
It destroyed me,
knowing what happened

25:44.440 --> 25:46.400
to the people on that flight.

25:46.440 --> 25:47.640
[sighs]

25:50.120 --> 25:52.480
All I could think about
every second of every day

25:52.520 --> 25:54.440
was those people.

25:54.480 --> 25:56.280
And you.

25:56.320 --> 25:57.800
Watching the news.

25:57.840 --> 26:00.720
And seeing the wreckage.

26:00.760 --> 26:03.320
I kept wondering
if I'd just said something,

26:03.360 --> 26:06.480
if it was my fault
so many innocent people died.

26:06.520 --> 26:08.800
[murmuring]

26:08.840 --> 26:11.640
-Miss.
-Oh, it crashed.

26:11.680 --> 26:13.920
-Miss, you okay?
-It crashed.

26:13.960 --> 26:17.840
They found the wreckage
an hour ago.

26:17.880 --> 26:20.880
WILL: So I asked Pieter
to check up on you.

26:20.920 --> 26:23.600
GEORGIA: That's why he was
at the airport, then?

26:23.640 --> 26:25.680
Azikiwe asked him to keep
an eye on Emmanuel Kazadi.

26:25.720 --> 26:27.560
It was his wife
that was carrying the bomb.

26:29.720 --> 26:32.680
He wanted to see
if she told him anything.

26:35.120 --> 26:37.040
Why didn't you call me?

26:38.080 --> 26:39.320
I did.

26:42.880 --> 26:44.080
A few times.

26:45.400 --> 26:47.800
I'd call and I just...

26:49.240 --> 26:51.440
And I just couldn't speak.

26:51.480 --> 26:54.080
I know you think
this is bullshit, Georgia,

26:54.120 --> 26:56.160
but in the weeks
after the crash,

26:56.200 --> 26:57.400
I couldn't function.

26:57.440 --> 26:59.920
And I was scared.

26:59.960 --> 27:03.000
You see, General Azikiwe has
men that are loyal to him--

27:03.040 --> 27:04.480
not to the government
but to him.

27:04.520 --> 27:06.320
So I hid.

27:06.360 --> 27:08.360
Mr. Bello.

27:09.520 --> 27:12.400
Mr. Bello, the general.

27:12.440 --> 27:15.520
You will speak
with General Azikiwe?

27:16.840 --> 27:19.440
I have nothing to do
with the general.

27:19.480 --> 27:22.400
And you know that, Kalehe.

27:22.440 --> 27:26.000
The people... the people,
they are angry.

27:26.040 --> 27:28.880
You speak with the general.

27:28.920 --> 27:30.680
I have my job.

27:30.720 --> 27:33.560
These soldiers,
they have their jobs.

27:33.600 --> 27:35.720
And you, you have your job.

27:35.760 --> 27:38.160
If you've got a problem
with Major General Azikiwe,

27:38.200 --> 27:40.240
you take it up
with him yourself.

27:40.280 --> 27:44.240
And good bloody luck.

27:44.280 --> 27:47.000
WILL: And Pieter hid me
right under their noses.

27:52.480 --> 27:56.000
I hid from Azikiwe in his own bloody coltan mine.

28:17.960 --> 28:19.960
[liquid sloshes]

28:23.920 --> 28:26.240
I've been protecting you
for long enough now.

28:26.280 --> 28:29.360
Azikiwe and Judith
both think you're dead.

28:32.200 --> 28:35.040
You can't hide out here forever.

28:35.080 --> 28:38.040
That plane was gonna go down
either way.

28:38.080 --> 28:39.960
No one was gonna stop it,
not you, not me.

28:40.000 --> 28:41.400
Is that what you tell yourself?

28:41.440 --> 28:43.920
It's not right,
knowing what we know.

28:43.960 --> 28:45.600
You want to go out there?

28:45.640 --> 28:47.520
You want to tell the world
what really happened?

28:47.560 --> 28:50.840
You want to see
how quickly you get dead?

28:53.000 --> 28:54.320
[sighs]

28:54.360 --> 28:55.520
Or Georgia?

28:55.560 --> 28:57.680
No, my brother.

28:57.720 --> 29:01.120
No. No, that's over.
Your old life is gone.

29:01.160 --> 29:03.120
She'll heal.

29:05.640 --> 29:07.560
We all do.

29:07.600 --> 29:09.360
You have to forget
about your old life.

29:09.400 --> 29:10.560
She's gone, bruv.

29:10.600 --> 29:12.960
Come on, up, up.
[grunts]

29:15.400 --> 29:16.960
Have you eaten?

29:17.000 --> 29:18.160
You're gonna need your strength.

29:18.200 --> 29:19.800
Why?

29:19.840 --> 29:22.160
'Cause the only way
I'm gonna keep you safe

29:22.200 --> 29:25.960
from Azikiwe is to get you
across the border.

29:26.000 --> 29:27.280
A long way from him.

29:27.320 --> 29:28.520
Come.

29:30.480 --> 29:33.680
[door creaks open]

29:33.720 --> 29:35.840
WILL:
I couldn't use my passport.

29:35.880 --> 29:37.600
I was declared dead.

29:37.640 --> 29:40.240
And I had no way out
of the DRC.

29:40.280 --> 29:41.760
I had no choice.

29:41.800 --> 29:44.240
General Azikiwe is
a fucking monster,

29:44.280 --> 29:47.320
I know he is,
but I can't undo what he did.

29:47.360 --> 29:50.120
Look.

29:50.160 --> 29:54.760
I... I know I'm a coward...
Georgia.

29:58.880 --> 30:01.800
But honestly I just thought
you'd be better off without me.

30:09.920 --> 30:12.760
[Adidja humming]

30:13.960 --> 30:15.960
[children chattering]

30:20.160 --> 30:22.040
[boys jeer]

30:22.080 --> 30:24.080
[boys yelling, chattering]

30:43.240 --> 30:45.000
Are you okay?

30:45.040 --> 30:48.960
This is no place to sleep.
It's not safe.

30:49.000 --> 30:52.160
Isn't there anyone looking
after you?

30:52.200 --> 30:53.400
It's fine.

30:55.040 --> 30:56.680
I made a mistake.

31:10.720 --> 31:12.520
GEORGIA:
Three years, Will.

31:12.560 --> 31:14.520
And what the hell is this?
Why are we talking

31:14.560 --> 31:17.640
with an armed guard
outside your house in Rwanda?

31:17.680 --> 31:19.600
WILL: Pieter got me out
of that mine and over here.

31:19.640 --> 31:22.280
And I, I don't know, I just...

31:24.800 --> 31:26.480
I just settled.

31:29.240 --> 31:31.360
I found work on a farm nearby.

31:33.440 --> 31:35.280
And I made a life for myself.

31:36.320 --> 31:39.640
Three years just...

31:39.680 --> 31:41.280
just passed by me,

31:41.320 --> 31:43.520
and all the guilt
and the paranoia just...

31:43.560 --> 31:45.880
It just started to fade,
you know.

31:45.920 --> 31:47.160
No, I don't know.

31:47.200 --> 31:48.720
If you're supposed to be hiding,

31:48.760 --> 31:51.440
-why go to Kinshasa?
-Okay, well, not so long ago

31:51.480 --> 31:52.960
Pieter came to see me,

31:53.000 --> 31:55.000
and he asked for my help.

31:59.280 --> 32:01.280
Well...

32:02.680 --> 32:04.800
-It's been a while, bru.
-Yeah, it has.

32:04.840 --> 32:06.280
[chuckling]:
It has.

32:06.320 --> 32:08.920
I went by your place,
they said you'd be here.

32:08.960 --> 32:10.920
I've had some bad news, bru.

32:10.960 --> 32:13.560
Um... HIV.

32:17.120 --> 32:19.080
I'm sorry to hear that.

32:19.120 --> 32:21.160
Well, they can treat HIV now.

32:21.200 --> 32:23.880
They can treat HIV now,
but, you know...

32:23.920 --> 32:26.560
the drugs out here--
very, very expensive.

32:26.600 --> 32:28.040
Veryexpensive.

32:28.080 --> 32:30.960
Also, I'm...
thinking about my daughter

32:31.000 --> 32:35.480
and... what I can do
to make things good for her.

32:35.520 --> 32:37.760
Mm-hmm.

32:37.800 --> 32:40.240
Six years.

32:40.280 --> 32:44.360
For six years
I've been making Judith Gray

32:44.400 --> 32:47.440
and General Azikiwe rich.

32:47.480 --> 32:49.920
Even after they
brought that plane down.

32:49.960 --> 32:52.520
Yeah. You've had enough?

32:52.560 --> 32:53.960
Well...

32:54.000 --> 32:56.320
the operation's not working
like it used to.

32:56.360 --> 32:58.520
Everybody wants a bigger piece.

32:58.560 --> 33:00.240
Somehow...

33:00.280 --> 33:02.760
I'm making less than I made
three years ago.

33:02.800 --> 33:04.520
And I need more.

33:04.560 --> 33:07.160
I want to stay alive.

33:07.200 --> 33:09.400
I'm gonna clean things up a bit.

33:09.440 --> 33:12.240
I'm gonna hire a militia group,

33:12.280 --> 33:14.080
and I'm gonna
take over the mine.

33:14.120 --> 33:18.560
You're taking on a mine
run by the Congolese army?

33:18.600 --> 33:21.920
What do I expect
from a Lions fan?

33:21.960 --> 33:23.480
[chuckling]

33:25.880 --> 33:27.840
I'm working with someone.

33:27.880 --> 33:29.120
There.

33:29.160 --> 33:32.240
Sidney Lagawa.
He works with Azikiwe.

33:32.280 --> 33:34.480
One of the few people
the general trusts.

33:34.520 --> 33:35.600
He's with us now.

33:35.640 --> 33:37.920
You keep saying "we."

33:37.960 --> 33:40.360
What do you expect from me?

33:40.400 --> 33:42.680
Okay.

33:42.720 --> 33:45.400
The money that Judith paid you,

33:45.440 --> 33:46.880
you put into account
in Kinshasa?

33:46.920 --> 33:48.200
Mm-hmm.

33:48.240 --> 33:50.400
Under a different name?

33:50.440 --> 33:52.480
If it's the money you want,
you can have it.

33:52.520 --> 33:54.160
I don't want anything
to do with that money.

33:54.200 --> 33:57.480
It makes me think
of the people on the flight.

33:57.520 --> 33:59.760
I can use that
to hire the militia.

33:59.800 --> 34:01.240
Done.

34:01.280 --> 34:05.960
But then you have
to come with me to Kinshasa.

34:06.000 --> 34:08.120
Oh, Pieter.

34:08.160 --> 34:09.760
I don't think
I can do it, Pieter.

34:09.800 --> 34:11.200
You're the only one that's
got access to that account.

34:11.240 --> 34:12.600
Yeah, okay.

34:12.640 --> 34:14.720
-We'll take precautions.
-I don't know, Pieter.

34:14.760 --> 34:17.040
-It's too risky.
-[speaks native language]

34:18.600 --> 34:20.280
I'm not the only one
that needs that money.

34:20.320 --> 34:22.320
You can use it, and I know that.

34:22.360 --> 34:25.600
And by the way, congratulations.

34:28.400 --> 34:30.040
Okay, I know that
I owe you, Pieter.

34:30.080 --> 34:31.560
I know that, all right?

34:31.600 --> 34:33.880
But it's not as easy as you say.

34:33.920 --> 34:36.040
I don't have a passport anymore,
I have no ID.

34:36.080 --> 34:38.440
I'm a man that can get
anything across the border.

34:38.480 --> 34:40.200
Yeah, and then we get
over the border, and then what?

34:40.240 --> 34:41.640
All the way to Kinshasa.

34:41.680 --> 34:44.560
And if I get caught, huh?
What happens then?

34:44.600 --> 34:48.080
One trip to Kinshasa.

34:48.120 --> 34:53.080
You help me
and you bring money home.

34:53.120 --> 34:55.520
A passport for a better life.

35:02.240 --> 35:04.560
Sidney, let's go.

35:08.760 --> 35:11.360
WILL: So I did what he asked.
I went to Kinshasa.

35:11.400 --> 35:12.960
[gunshots]

35:13.000 --> 35:15.040
[panicked shouting]

35:15.080 --> 35:17.120
WILL:
While we were in the bank,
a government protest

35:17.160 --> 35:19.520
blew up into a fucking
full-scale riot.

35:19.560 --> 35:21.840
It happened so fast.

35:21.880 --> 35:23.040
Jesus Christ.

35:23.080 --> 35:24.040
I didn't think
we'd make it out of there.

35:24.080 --> 35:25.040
We're blocked.

35:25.080 --> 35:26.200
We have to get
across that street,

35:26.240 --> 35:27.560
and we'll get out of here.

35:27.600 --> 35:29.040
With a bag full of money
in the middle of a riot?

35:29.080 --> 35:30.880
You want to say that louder?!

35:30.920 --> 35:34.080
Keep your head down, stay calm,
and we'll walk out of here.

35:34.120 --> 35:35.720
-Stay calm.
-[gunfire]

35:35.760 --> 35:38.360
Oh, God.

35:38.400 --> 35:40.160
Come on, Will. All right, go.

35:40.200 --> 35:41.760
Will, go!

35:41.800 --> 35:43.200
Jesus Christ.

35:43.240 --> 35:45.120
[sirens blaring]

35:45.160 --> 35:48.840
Come on. Come on, Will!
Stay with me.

35:48.880 --> 35:50.320
Come on.

35:50.360 --> 35:53.160
[shouting and gunfire]

35:55.800 --> 35:57.720
Pieter!

35:57.760 --> 35:59.760
Will!

35:59.800 --> 36:02.360
[woman screaming]

36:02.400 --> 36:04.400
Come here, Will!

36:14.440 --> 36:16.720
Fuck!

36:16.760 --> 36:18.680
[panting]

36:20.560 --> 36:22.920
PIETER:
Will! Will!

36:22.960 --> 36:25.200
Come on, Will.
Come on.

36:26.400 --> 36:28.320
Come on, Will.

36:28.360 --> 36:30.720
No, no, no, no, no.
Will!

36:30.760 --> 36:32.280
This way. Come.

36:34.440 --> 36:37.120
All right, keep moving.
Keep moving.

36:38.400 --> 36:39.560
Go straight ahead.

36:39.600 --> 36:42.080
No, don't stop.
Keep going.

36:42.120 --> 36:44.440
[panting]

37:01.280 --> 37:03.960
See? What did I tell you?

37:04.000 --> 37:05.840
Piece of cake.

37:05.880 --> 37:07.920
I still need to get back
across the border.

37:07.960 --> 37:09.720
It'll be fine.

37:09.760 --> 37:10.680
Business class.

37:10.720 --> 37:12.760
Come on. This way.

37:21.200 --> 37:23.040
Thank you.

37:24.400 --> 37:27.080
Hey, Will, you ready?

37:27.120 --> 37:29.240
Nope.

37:29.280 --> 37:31.280
The way out was bad enough.

37:31.320 --> 37:32.920
Here.

37:32.960 --> 37:35.120
What's this for?

37:35.160 --> 37:37.760
It's a good luck charm.
It's for you.

37:40.120 --> 37:41.360
Hey, you okay?

37:41.400 --> 37:43.120
Yeah.
We'll have to leave you here

37:43.160 --> 37:45.560
until the driver gets here.

37:45.600 --> 37:47.320
I'll wait from nearby.
Here.

37:49.280 --> 37:52.040
Well, go on. Fimi's gonna be
wondering where we are.

37:52.080 --> 37:53.680
We'll go straight through,
no stopping.

38:06.120 --> 38:08.040
WILL: I hired the guard
when I returned.

38:08.080 --> 38:10.880
Going back to Kinshasa, it just brought everything back,

38:10.920 --> 38:12.920
-all the paranoia.
-[drill whirring]

38:12.960 --> 38:14.840
I was worried they'd find me,

38:14.880 --> 38:18.400
and I felt I had
to protect myself.

38:18.440 --> 38:21.280
Was it worth it?

38:22.320 --> 38:25.200
Honestly, um...

38:25.240 --> 38:28.280
uh...

38:28.320 --> 38:30.320
no.

38:34.080 --> 38:37.760
I don't know.
I didn't mean to...

38:37.800 --> 38:41.120
I didn't plan any of this,
George, I was just...

38:41.160 --> 38:43.320
putting one foot in front
of the other, trying to survive.

38:43.360 --> 38:44.960
I...

38:45.000 --> 38:47.560
-We both were after Violet.
-Please.

38:47.600 --> 38:49.800
-[voice breaking]: Please don't.
-I'm sorry, but it's true.

38:49.840 --> 38:52.480
I couldn't cope.

38:57.200 --> 38:59.360
I wasn't there for you.

39:05.360 --> 39:07.920
I couldn't...

39:07.960 --> 39:10.920
Hey. Hey.

39:12.920 --> 39:15.440
I still think about her.

39:15.480 --> 39:17.400
Every day.

39:17.440 --> 39:19.480
Yeah.

39:20.480 --> 39:22.640
Sorry.

39:22.680 --> 39:25.880
-It's so weird seeing your face.
-Yeah.

39:25.920 --> 39:30.240
Hey, and I know
with what's happened,

39:30.280 --> 39:33.040
everything that I've done,

39:33.080 --> 39:35.560
I know it's impossible
to believe me, but, Georgie,

39:35.600 --> 39:37.600
I didn't just...

39:37.640 --> 39:40.920
I didn't just stop loving you.

39:43.920 --> 39:46.920
I've thought
about you every day.

39:53.560 --> 39:55.520
Hey.

39:56.560 --> 39:58.560
[grunts]

40:00.800 --> 40:03.840
So, what do we do now?

40:05.360 --> 40:08.320
[exhales]

40:08.360 --> 40:10.320
[door opens]

40:16.760 --> 40:18.840
-Hey.
-Fimi's asleep.

40:18.880 --> 40:21.760
Okay, yeah, yeah.

40:21.800 --> 40:24.120
-Come here.
-[sighs]

40:28.640 --> 40:30.640
[Fimi fussing]

40:41.640 --> 40:44.640
Gloria, this is Georgia.

40:56.640 --> 40:58.640
Okay.

41:00.000 --> 41:04.200
Now I get it. Now I get it.

41:16.200 --> 41:18.160
Georgie!

41:20.520 --> 41:22.600
-Hey, Georgie.
-No. No.

41:22.640 --> 41:24.080
Just stop.

41:24.120 --> 41:26.800
Finally I understand.

41:26.840 --> 41:28.520
-What?
-Oh.

41:28.560 --> 41:30.040
It's always just been

41:30.080 --> 41:32.040
the path of least resistance
for you, hasn't it?

41:33.560 --> 41:35.200
You just couldn't
tell me straight, could you?

41:36.280 --> 41:39.880
God, I'm so fucking stupid.

41:39.920 --> 41:42.840
That is why you couldn't
call me, isn't it?

41:42.880 --> 41:45.200
That's why you spent
so much time over here.

41:47.920 --> 41:50.160
How old's the baby?

41:50.200 --> 41:52.600
Look, you don't understand...

41:52.640 --> 41:54.640
How old?

41:56.720 --> 41:59.080
She's a few months old.

42:01.120 --> 42:03.160
Same age.

42:03.200 --> 42:05.280
Hey.

42:05.320 --> 42:07.640
What was it?
Was it easier, was it?

42:07.680 --> 42:10.920
Just too much baggage?
The old relationship's broken,

42:10.960 --> 42:13.080
so you just throw it in the dirt
and get rid of it.

42:14.240 --> 42:17.920
After everything
I've fucking done for you!

42:17.960 --> 42:20.920
People are dead because of you.

42:23.320 --> 42:26.400
I don't know you at all, do I?

42:28.680 --> 42:31.880
I don't think I ever did.

42:31.920 --> 42:33.800
-Just...
-Stop.

42:35.840 --> 42:37.880
Go home, Will.

42:39.400 --> 42:41.400
[breathing heavily]

